<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 777/94 of 29 March 1994 derogating from Regulation (EEC) No 1637/91 as regards the payment of compensation to milk producers for the reduction of reference quantities </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 777/94, milles kehtestatakse erand m&auml;&auml;rusest (EM&Uuml;) nr 1637/91 seoses kvootide v&auml;hendamise puhul piimatootjatele h&uuml;vitise maksmisega 29.m&auml;rts 1994 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having reagard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1637/91 (3) introduces in particular a Community scheme to finance the definitive discontinuation of milk production and provides, where certain eligibility requirements are met, for compensation to be paid after the definitive discontinuation of all milk production not later than 31 March 1992; whereas that Regulation contains in its Annex a financial amount per Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1637/91 (3) kehtestatakse eelk&otilde;ige &uuml;henduse kava piimatootmisest l&otilde;plikult loobumise rahastamiseks ja n&auml;hakse teatavate n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise korral ette h&uuml;vitis, mis makstakse p&auml;rast piimatootmisest l&otilde;plikult loobumist hiljemalt 31. m&auml;rtsil 1992; k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas on s&auml;testatud summad liikmesriigi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 2 (5) of that Regulation provides that, in cases where the financial amounts are not entirely used up, the amounts remaining available are to be used for the payment of compensation to all of the producers whose reference quantity has been reduced; whereas in certain Member States, this provision has prevented Community financing from continuing to be allocated to the scheme for the definitive discontinuation of milk production; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 2 l&otilde;ikega 5 n&auml;hakse ette, et juhul kui summasid ei kasutata t&auml;ielikult, kasutatakse allesj&auml;&auml;nud summasid h&uuml;vitise maksmiseks k&otilde;ikidele tootjatele, kelle kvooti on v&auml;hendatud; teatavates liikmesriikides on k&otilde;nealune s&auml;te takistanud &uuml;henduse abi andmist piimatootmisest l&otilde;plikult loobumise kava rahastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Council, by means of Regulation (EEC) No 1560/93 amending Regulation (EEC) No 3950/92 establishing an additional levy in the milk products sector (4), allocated a contribution of ECU 40 million to the national programmes for the definitive discontinuation of milk production; whereas the present situation requires, in several respects, that the national reserves be replenished; whereas, as a result, provision should be made for the possibility of derogating from Article 2 (5) of Regulation (EEC) No 1637/91 in order to re-allocate to the national programmes for the definitive discontinuation of milk production the amount remaining available under Community financing provided for the payment of compensation to all producers, </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu eraldas m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1560/93, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3950/92 (millega kehtestatakse piimatootesektoris lisamaks), (4) piimatoomisest l&otilde;plikult loobumise riiklike programmide jaoks 40 miljonit ek&uuml;&uuml;d; praegune olukord n&otilde;uab mitmel p&otilde;hjusel riigi varude t&auml;iendamist; sellest tulenevalt tuleks s&auml;testada v&otilde;imalus teha erand m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1637/91 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikest 5, et jaotada k&otilde;ikidele tootjatele h&uuml;vitise maksmiseks etten&auml;htud &uuml;henduse rahastamise raames allesj&auml;&auml;nud summa &uuml;mber piimatoodangust l&otilde;plikult loobumise riiklikele programmidele; </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the first subparagraph of Article 2 (5) of Regulation (EEC) No 1637/91, the Member States concerned may also use the amounts remaining available to pay, in accordance with the first indent of the first subparagraph of Article 8 of Regulation (EEC) No 3950/92 and the request of interested producers, compensation the maximum amount of which that may be covered by Community financing shall be ECU 10 per 100 kilograms and per year. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1637/91 artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 5 esimesest l&otilde;igust, v&otilde;ivad asjaomased liikmesriigid samuti kasutada allesj&auml;&auml;nud summasid, et maksta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3950/92 artikli 8 esimese l&otilde;igu esimese taande kohaselt ja huvitatud tootja taotluse korral h&uuml;vitist, mille &uuml;henduse poolt rahastatav &uuml;lemm&auml;&auml;r on 10 ek&uuml;&uuml;d 100 kg kohta aastas. </eesti>
<inglise> The quantities thus freed shall be re-allocated to the producers referred to in Article 1 of Regulation (EEC) No 1637/91, unless they elect to receive the compensation as originally provided for in the first subparagraph of Article 2 (5) of that Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel viisil vabanenud kvoodid jaotatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1637/91 artiklis 1 osutatud tootjate vahel &uuml;mber, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui k&otilde;nealused tootjad soovivad saada k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 5 esimese l&otilde;iguga etten&auml;htud h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 29 March 1994. </inglise>
